House of Representatives Member representing Sumaila/Takai Federal constituency of Kano state, Hon. Shamsudeen Dambazau has expressed grief and sadness over the passing of Emir of Rano, Alhaji Tafida Abubakar Ila Auta Bawo. In a statement condoling with the Kano State Government, Council of Chiefs and indeed the people of the emirate, Dambazau described the royal father’s demise as a personal loss to him particularly and an even greater loss to the people of Kano State and Nigeria in general. He further described the emir as someone, whose words of wisdom, nobility, and decency will be sorely missed, especially at a time the nation was increasingly looking up to the traditional stool as the moral compass for the people. “I am particularly saddened over the passing of our royal father who was not just a traditional ruler to me but a father figure as well. “Upon my being elected to the Federal House of Representatives, it afforded me the opportunity to seek his counsel often as I sought to better the lives of my constituents who fall under his emirate.’ The statement further called on the Kano government and Emirate to find solace in the good works of the deceased and ensure his legacies are carried on. Hon. Dambazau prayed Allah to forgive the shortcomings of the Emir, remember his good works and grant his soul eternal rest.”